news.title: Ahmedabad elevated to higher-risk quake zone; realty braces for 25% cost shock
news.para: Ahmedabad has been upgraded to Seismic Zone IV by the Bureau of Indian Standards, effective May 3, 2026. This change mandates stronger structural designs for new buildings, requiring increased material usage. Industry experts anticipate a 20-25% rise in new property prices due to these enhanced construction standards.

news.title: Hyderabad: Auro Realty acquires Taj Banjara for ₹315 crore
news.para: Aurobindo Group's realty arm, Auro Realty, has acquired the iconic Taj Banjara hotel in Hyderabad for ₹315 crore. The deal marks the end of operations for one of the city's first five-star hotels, which has been closed since its lease expired in 2023.

news.title: Uttarakhand cabinet okays proposal for resort building on farmland without land use change
news.para: The Uttarakhand cabinet has taken significant steps towards enhancing the tourism sector by approving agricultural land for resort development without altering its designated use. The new regulations stipulate that roads in hilly areas must be at least six meters wide, while those in plains should be nine meters.

news.title: Jammu & Kashmir RERA proposes single window system for integrated approvals
news.para: In a bid to streamline real estate processes, the Jammu and Kashmir Real Estate Regulatory Authority is introducing a consolidated single window system for project approvals and registrations. Accompanying this initiative are district-level enforcement teams tasked with monitoring compliance and rectifying any violations.

news.title: Expect SIT to probe past CEOs of Noida authority: SC
news.para: The Supreme Court has broadened the scope of a Special Investigation Team (SIT) inquiry into NOIDA officials. This expanded inquiry will now delve into the actions of past chief executive officers and other high-ranking officials suspected of colluding to inflate land compensation payments. Notably, farmers who are receiving these inflated amounts will not be penalized.

news.title: JSW Paints acquires 61.2% stake in Akzo Nobel India
news.para: JSW Paints has acquired a 61.2% stake in Akzo Nobel India, marking one of the largest deals in the paints sector and strengthening its position in decorative and industrial coatings.

news.title: Pune land deal: Is police protecting deputy CM's son Parth Pawar? asks Bombay HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court has raised significant concerns regarding the police investigation into a high-stakes land deal in Pune, indicating possible favoritism towards Parth Pawar, the son of Deputy Chief Minister Ajit Pawar. The transaction, involving 40 acres of land sold for an astonishing Rs 300 crore, has drawn scrutiny since the land was allegedly government-owned and not for sale.

news.title: Berkeley's pre-tax profit falls 7.7% to $338 million in H1
news.para: Homebuilder Berkeley stands firm on its yearly financial projections, despite experiencing decreased profits and a slump in home deliveries over the past six months. However, with optimism surrounding the London property market, the company is poised for improvement. Innovative strategies to expedite construction in the capital are on the way, alongside an anticipated build-to-rent platform launching in 2026.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT raises ₹3,500 crore via QIP to fund expansion, debt reduction
news.para: Brookfield India REIT has made headlines by raising ₹3,500 crore via a qualified institutional placement, indicating a high level of investor interest. This capital will play a crucial role in expanding their portfolio, especially with the noteworthy acquisition of Ecoworld in Bengaluru on the horizon.

news.title: Ridhira Group, Sumadhura sign MoUs with Telangana for projects worth ₹717 crore
news.para: Telangana is gearing up for a transformative era as major investments take center stage. The Ridhira Group is allocating ₹117 crore to develop a premier hospitality project, while the Sumadhura Group has pledged an impressive ₹600 crore towards a vast industrial park.

news.title: Ghost malls across 32 cities offer ₹357 crore annual rental potential: Report
news.para: A striking report highlights that there are 74 ghost malls scattered across India, with 15 of them having the potential to generate a whopping ₹357 crore annually if they undergo revitalization. The highest rental returns can be found in Tier-1 cities, making these areas prime real estate havens.

news.title: SM REIT market in India projected to surpass $75 billion: CBRE
news.para: India's booming SM REITs market is poised for massive growth, with estimates reaching a whopping 75 billion US dollars. These Real Estate Investment Trusts, backed by over 500 million square feet of office, logistics, and retail spaces, are totally changing how people invest in commercial real estate.

news.title: Cement makers' margins to rise 250-300 bps on higher realisations, stable costs: Crisil
news.para: Cement manufacturers in India are gearing up for a remarkable surge in operating margins this fiscal year. A rise in sales volume coupled with consistent input costs is fueling optimism. Nationwide cement prices are expected to hold steady, and while GST adjustments may lead to retail price fluctuations, producers are poised for favorable monetary gains.

news.title: Bhubaneswar development body carries out eviction drives in Patia, Kalarahanga
news.para: Bhubaneswar Development Authority (BDA) has intensified its anti-encroachment drives, clearing significant government land in Patia and Kalarahanga.  Demolitions included boundary walls, concrete structures, and shops, freeing hundreds of decimals of land.  These actions follow revelations of widespread government land grabs, aiming to curb illegal occupation and ease public access.

news.title: Ranchi civic body to enforce strict regulations on commercial activities
news.para: In an effort to bolster city revenues and regulate commercial activities, Ranchi Municipal Corporation is intensifying its scrutiny of city advertising displays. A comprehensive review of all hoardings is underway, and those failing to meet regulations will face penalties.

news.title: Surat civic body speeds up land acquisition for multi-modal transport hub project
news.para: Surat Municipal Corporation is speeding up land acquisition for the Multi-Modal Transport Hub. Construction of the bus terminal is nearing completion. The elevated road corridor is also progressing. Officials are directed to fast-track land handover and ensure project facilities. The project involves multiple government bodies for smooth execution.

news.title: Telangana looks at PPP model for providing affordable housing
news.para: Telangana aims to provide every family with a decent home by 2047, with a new housing policy focusing on economic viability, environmental responsibility, and technology. Experts urge a return to smaller, low-cost homes and development beyond the Outer Ring Road to address a significant housing shortage. Developers call for regulatory adjustments and government support to make affordable housing a reality.

news.title: Dues not paid under rehab policy, Greater Noida authority to crack down on builders
news.para: Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority is withdrawing benefits from defaulting builders to revive stalled projects, having recovered Rs 1,382 crore. The authority has hired Currie and Brown for physical assessments of projects, categorizing them based on payment status and legal standing to determine the next course of action.

news.title: About 7,000 returnable plots in Amaravati yet to be registered: Andhra Pradesh municipal minister
news.para: Ongoing efforts are being made to register returnable plots for farmers in Amaravati, with Minister P Narayana revealing that 7,000 plots have not yet been registered. However, the government is committed to facilitating these registrations and promises to have infrastructure in place within two years.

news.title: Hong Kong's Lai Sun Development sells stake in central office tower for $450 million
news.para: Lai Sun Development is parting ways with its share of an office tower in Hong Kong, listing it for HK$3.5 billion. This decisive action is intended to enhance the company's cash reserves during a period of significant financial strains, marked by plummeting property sales and limited access to financing.
